Takako Konishi, 28, travelled half-way across the world to try and find a suitcase stuffed with $1m worth of cash buried in the frozen wastes of Minnesota Lakes .
She was found dead in a mini-skirt and high-heeled boots in the freezing wastes .
Her story has been made into a film of its own - Kumiko, the Treasure Hunter - which dramatizes the myth of her journey and sad end .